[
    {
        "text": "Hello everyone, this is Minoo at Anglo-Link.",
        "start": 0.48,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "Welcome to lesson 12 in my Ezee series where \nwe will be dealing with two more common words",
        "start": 8.4,
        "duration": 6.96
    },
    {
        "text": "that often lead to confusion and mistakes.",
        "start": 15.36,
        "duration": 3.642
    },
    {
        "text": "Getting rid of confusion and starting to correct your own mistakes",
        "start": 19.002,
        "duration": 4.933
    },
    {
        "text": "is one of the best things you can do to speak\nEnglish more confidently.",
        "start": 23.935,
        "duration": 5.802
    },
    {
        "text": "So, in today's lesson we're going to clear up the \nconfusion many of us experience with the words:",
        "start": 29.737,
        "duration": 7.65
    },
    {
        "text": "'good' and 'well'",
        "start": 37.387,
        "duration": 2.738
    },
    {
        "text": "Should  we say I'm good or I'm well?",
        "start": 40.125,
        "duration": 5.017
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's go over to the lesson to find out how to use these two words correctly.",
        "start": 45.142,
        "duration": 6.277
    },
    {
        "text": "Easy to Zap English Errors lesson 12.",
        "start": 52.753,
        "duration": 3.545
    },
    {
        "text": "Good or well?",
        "start": 56.917,
        "duration": 1.718
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's see what we're going to be doing in this lesson.",
        "start": 59.703,
        "duration": 2.691
    },
    {
        "text": "We'll start with a test yourself quiz.",
        "start": 62.394,
        "duration": 3.193
    },
    {
        "text": "Then we'll look at when to use good.",
        "start": 65.587,
        "duration": 3.15
    },
    {
        "text": "Then we'll look at when to use well.",
        "start": 68.737,
        "duration": 2.932
    },
    {
        "text": "And we'll end with a final quiz.",
        "start": 71.669,
        "duration": 3.482
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay let's start with your test yourself quiz.",
        "start": 76.24,
        "duration": 3.656
    },
    {
        "text": "I'd like you to choose the best two answers to...",
        "start": 80.571,
        "duration": 3.669
    },
    {
        "text": "Hi how are you doing?",
        "start": 84.24,
        "duration": 1.925
    },
    {
        "text": "out of these four answers.",
        "start": 86.165,
        "duration": 2.737
    },
    {
        "text": "The first one...",
        "start": 89.216,
        "duration": 1.341
    },
    {
        "text": "Good, thanks.",
        "start": 90.557,
        "duration": 1.753
    },
    {
        "text": "Very well, thank you.",
        "start": 93.236,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": " I'm doing good, thanks.",
        "start": 96.305,
        "duration": 2.572
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm doing well, thank you.",
        "start": 100.494,
        "duration": 2.383
    },
    {
        "text": "Which of these four answers do you think are the best?",
        "start": 104.32,
        "duration": 5.442
    },
    {
        "text": "The best ones are 'a' and 'b'.",
        "start": 112.32,
        "duration": 3.014
    },
    {
        "text": "'Good thanks' and 'very well thank you'.",
        "start": 115.334,
        "duration": 3.136
    },
    {
        "text": "Although you may hear the other two as well sometimes,",
        "start": 119.192,
        "duration": 3.852
    },
    {
        "text": "'a' and 'b' are the better ones.",
        "start": 123.373,
        "duration": 2.552
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's see why.",
        "start": 125.925,
        "duration": 1.777
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's start by looking at when to use 'good'.",
        "start": 129.411,
        "duration": 3.287
    },
    {
        "text": "'Good' is an adjective and is used to describe \na noun which can be something or someone.",
        "start": 134.32,
        "duration": 6.08
    },
    {
        "text": "For example:",
        "start": 141.44,
        "duration": 1.385
    },
    {
        "text": "This approach is good. \nHere, 'good' is describing something,",
        "start": 143.076,
        "duration": 5.279
    },
    {
        "text": "an approach.",
        "start": 148.355,
        "duration": 1.504
    },
    {
        "text": "Or...",
        "start": 150.285,
        "duration": 0.959
    },
    {
        "text": "Linda is a good employee.",
        "start": 151.542,
        "duration": 2.376
    },
    {
        "text": "Here, good is describing someone.",
        "start": 154.232,
        "duration": 3.272
    },
    {
        "text": "Linda.",
        "start": 157.959,
        "duration": 1.498
    },
    {
        "text": "So when someone greets you by \nsaying:",
        "start": 160.8,
        "duration": 2.873
    },
    {
        "text": "Hi, how are you doing?",
        "start": 163.673,
        "duration": 2.167
    },
    {
        "text": "Or...",
        "start": 165.84,
        "duration": 0.915
    },
    {
        "text": "Hello, how are you?",
        "start": 166.755,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "You can describe your state by using good.",
        "start": 170.0,
        "duration": 3.177
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'm good'.",
        "start": 173.694,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "You're describing yourself.",
        "start": 175.084,
        "duration": 1.765
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'",
        "start": 177.147,
        "duration": 1.502
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also say: 'I'm fine',",
        "start": 179.306,
        "duration": 3.016
    },
    {
        "text": "which means you are in good health and or in a good mood.",
        "start": 182.84,
        "duration": 6.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Now in informal English, in response to \n'how are you doing?' you may sometimes hear:",
        "start": 191.76,
        "duration": 6.08
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'm doing good'.",
        "start": 198.64,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "But, because good is not an adverb,",
        "start": 200.926,
        "duration": 2.911
    },
    {
        "text": "This sentence is grammatically incorrect.",
        "start": 203.837,
        "duration": 3.246
    },
    {
        "text": "If you want to use 'i'm doing' in your reply,",
        "start": 208.72,
        "duration": 3.344
    },
    {
        "text": "it's better to use 'fine'",
        "start": 212.064,
        "duration": 2.119
    },
    {
        "text": "because fine is both an adjective and an adverb.",
        "start": 214.183,
        "duration": 4.721
    },
    {
        "text": "So, instead of saying 'I'm doing good' say:",
        "start": 219.058,
        "duration": 3.34
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'm doing fine'.",
        "start": 222.398,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay! Let's look at how to use 'well'.",
        "start": 227.251,
        "duration": 4.843
    },
    {
        "text": "Well is the adverb form of good.",
        "start": 233.2,
        "duration": 2.689
    },
    {
        "text": "As an adverb, it describes an action.",
        "start": 235.889,
        "duration": 2.862
    },
    {
        "text": "'This approach works'.",
        "start": 239.52,
        "duration": 1.862
    },
    {
        "text": "Works is a verb an action.",
        "start": 241.382,
        "duration": 2.268
    },
    {
        "text": "'well'.",
        "start": 243.65,
        "duration": 1.589
    },
    {
        "text": "Linda has done her job",
        "start": 246.4,
        "duration": 2.465
    },
    {
        "text": "'done' is an action",
        "start": 248.865,
        "duration": 2.127
    },
    {
        "text": "therefore, 'well'.",
        "start": 250.992,
        "duration": 2.439
    },
    {
        "text": "But well is also an adjective which means \nnot ill or in good health.",
        "start": 255.12,
        "duration": 5.356
    },
    {
        "text": "So you can also say:",
        "start": 260.664,
        "duration": 1.855
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'm well'.",
        "start": 262.817,
        "duration": 1.726
    },
    {
        "text": "Here your reply is specifically in the \ncontext of your health rather than your mood.",
        "start": 265.0,
        "duration": 7.414
    },
    {
        "text": "So, when someone greets you by saying:",
        "start": 275.297,
        "duration": 2.398
    },
    {
        "text": "'how are you' or? 'how are you doing?' you can say:",
        "start": 277.695,
        "duration": 4.304
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'm very well thank you.'",
        "start": 281.999,
        "duration": 1.426
    },
    {
        "text": "Or 'very well, thank you'",
        "start": 283.425,
        "duration": 2.195
    },
    {
        "text": "But these days the most common answers are:",
        "start": 286.797,
        "duration": 3.348
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'm good thanks.'",
        "start": 290.145,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "'Fine, thank you.'",
        "start": 293.479,
        "duration": 1.606
    },
    {
        "text": "And if someone asks you specifically about how you're recovering from an illness or succeeding in a task",
        "start": 296.595,
        "duration": 7.311
    },
    {
        "text": "then you can answer:",
        "start": 303.906,
        "duration": 2.058
    },
    {
        "text": "'I'm doing well' or 'I'm doing fine.'",
        "start": 305.964,
        "duration": 4.897
    },
    {
        "text": "Right! it's time for our final quiz.",
        "start": 311.505,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "I'd like you to decide if there's a mistake \nin the sentence, and if there is, correct it.",
        "start": 316.364,
        "duration": 6.085
    },
    {
        "text": "Number 1:",
        "start": 323.2,
        "duration": 1.232
    },
    {
        "text": "'how's your son doing at school?'",
        "start": 325.0,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "'He's doing good.'",
        "start": 327.471,
        "duration": 1.432
    },
    {
        "text": "Is this correct?",
        "start": 328.903,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "No it isn't because we're asking about someone's \nperformance at school.",
        "start": 333.347,
        "duration": 5.289
    },
    {
        "text": "So, we shouldn't use the adjective 'good' but the adverb 'well'.",
        "start": 338.636,
        "duration": 5.911
    },
    {
        "text": "'How's your son doing at school?'",
        "start": 344.83,
        "duration": 1.922
    },
    {
        "text": "'He's doing well.'",
        "start": 346.752,
        "duration": 2.085
    },
    {
        "text": "Number 2:",
        "start": 350.72,
        "duration": 1.418
    },
    {
        "text": "How's your mum? I heard she was ill.",
        "start": 352.828,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "'She's good again'.",
        "start": 356.241,
        "duration": 1.872
    },
    {
        "text": "Is this correct?",
        "start": 358.803,
        "duration": 1.868
    },
    {
        "text": "Again, it is not correct.",
        "start": 362.711,
        "duration": 2.001
    },
    {
        "text": "It's incorrect because we are asking about someone's health,",
        "start": 364.712,
        "duration": 5.288
    },
    {
        "text": "and therefore, we can't use the word 'good'.",
        "start": 370.425,
        "duration": 3.718
    },
    {
        "text": "But the adjective 'well'. 'She's well again'.",
        "start": 374.143,
        "duration": 4.448
    },
    {
        "text": "And the last one.",
        "start": 380.373,
        "duration": 1.179
    },
    {
        "text": "Number 3:",
        "start": 381.552,
        "duration": 1.514
    },
    {
        "text": "'Hi, how are you all doing?'",
        "start": 383.411,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "'We're all good, thanks.'",
        "start": 386.888,
        "duration": 2.479
    },
    {
        "text": "Is this correct?",
        "start": 389.901,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "It is because we are asking about \neveryone's health or mood in general.",
        "start": 395.556,
        "duration": 7.12
    },
    {
        "text": "And therefore, here we can use the \nadjective 'good'.",
        "start": 402.676,
        "duration": 4.608
    },
    {
        "text": "'We're all good, thanks'.",
        "start": 407.284,
        "duration": 3.051
    },
    {
        "text": "Well that is the end of lesson 12.",
        "start": 412.326,
        "duration": 3.199
    },
    {
        "text": "I hope your doubts about 'good' and 'well' have been cleared up.",
        "start": 415.776,
        "duration": 5.405
    },
    {
        "text": "For an in-depth lesson on the use of adjectives and adverbs",
        "start": 421.244,
        "duration": 4.676
    },
    {
        "text": "visit my Youtube channel and look for the \nvideo adjectives and adverbs",
        "start": 426.48,
        "duration": 6.457
    },
    {
        "text": "or use the link at the end of this video.",
        "start": 432.937,
        "duration": 3.23
    },
    {
        "text": "I'd also like to invite you to check out my online self-study course",
        "start": 436.167,
        "duration": 5.17
    },
    {
        "text": "that will help you to improve your writing and \nspeaking skills using a step-by-step approach.",
        "start": 441.337,
        "duration": 7.575
    },
    {
        "text": "You can sign up for my online course \nby visiting my website",
        "start": 449.68,
        "duration": 4.689
    },
    {
        "text": "Anglo-Link.com.",
        "start": 454.369,
        "duration": 2.832
    },
    {
        "text": "Also please remember to subscribe to my channel and allow notifications to know when  my next lesson is available.",
        "start": 458.56,
        "duration": 8.428
    },
    {
        "text": "Thank you for your continued support, and I hope to see you again soon.",
        "start": 467.773,
        "duration": 5.637
    },
    {
        "text": "Goodbye for now.",
        "start": 473.849,
        "duration": 2.548
    }
]